you'll be stuck with me.

262
00:12:04,633 --> 00:12:07,200
Oh, my...

263
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:09,667
Have you seen their menu here?

264
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,433
Baby back ribs, that's what
we're going to order.

265
00:12:11,567 --> 00:12:13,033
Okay, Sir, okay.

266
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,067
Three thousand?

267
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,667
Sir, that's expensive.

268
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,900
Let's just order something else.

269
00:12:22,033 --> 00:12:23,400
I'll have soup.

270
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:24,500
I'll have this, Sir.

271
00:12:24,633 --> 00:12:26,867
No, let's order baby back ribs.

272
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:27,967
Waiter.

273
00:12:28,100 --> 00:12:30,133
That's our budget for the week.

274
00:12:30,267 --> 00:12:31,367
That's delicious here.

275
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:34,367
Two baby back ribs.

276
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:36,667
What drinks are you having?

277
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:39,333
Okay, Mr. Balad, thank you.

278
00:12:39,467 --> 00:12:41,300
We'll just call you if we need
anything else.

279
00:12:41,433 --> 00:12:42,767
Thank you.

280
00:12:49,533 --> 00:12:50,600
What, Bok?

281
00:12:50,733 --> 00:12:52,967
Let's go see Jared.

282
00:12:53,100 --> 00:12:58,233
He's not there because he and
Bobby are dating right now.

283
00:12:58,367 --> 00:13:00,967
Bobby, answer the phone.

284
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,633
Bro, if she's dating Bobby,

285
00:13:03,767 --> 00:13:05,033
she won't answer.

286
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:14,900
Jared, sorry,

287
00:13:15,033 --> 00:13:17,500
I'll get straight to it.

288
00:13:19,333 --> 00:13:21,900
I've got a lot going on
in my life right now.

289
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:23,500
It's a bit chaotic,

290
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:28,900
and you still
don't know me that well.

291
00:13:29,033 --> 00:13:31,633
That's okay, I get it.

292
00:13:31,767 --> 00:13:33,000
You still like Tonyo.

293
00:13:33,133 --> 00:13:34,667
Hey, no!

294
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,367
No, Sir. No, no.

295
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:38,533
So you don't like Tonyo?

296
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:40,267
It's not like that...

297
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,300
Oh...

298
00:13:41,433 --> 00:13:42,867
Then, what?

299
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:46,833
Okay.

300
00:13:48,733 --> 00:13:50,633
Sir, I'll admit
something to you.

301
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,767
It's Abdul.

302
00:13:54,933 --> 00:13:56,967
Call Abdul.

303
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:57,867
Yes, call him.

304
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:00,200
Maybe they know where Bobby is.

305
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:10,433
Delicious, right?

306
00:14:10,567 --> 00:14:11,967
Well, it should be, Sir.

307
00:14:12,100 --> 00:14:13,800
If this isn't delicious,
I'll sue them.

308
00:14:18,667 --> 00:14:19,367
Bobby...

309
00:14:21,333 --> 00:14:23,300
have you and Tonyo
talked lately?

310
00:14:26,933 --> 00:14:28,033
Oh, yes, Sir.

311
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,233
He called earlier
when I was on my way here.

312
00:14:38,333 --> 00:14:41,567
It's a long story about Tonyo,
Sir.

313
00:14:41,700 --> 00:14:44,267
And it's a bit complicated.

314
00:14:50,767 --> 00:14:53,167
But we're not together, Sir.

315
00:14:53,300 --> 00:14:55,300
Well, I wish we were a couple,

316
00:14:55,433 --> 00:14:57,933
but we're not.

317
00:15:01,933 --> 00:15:03,733
Actually, I'm not interested

318
00:15:03,867 --> 00:15:06,867
in your story with Tonyo.

319
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,767
And,

320
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:11,767
I know this might be too soon
for you,

321
00:15:11,900 --> 00:15:14,100
but it's obvious to me.

322
00:15:14,233 --> 00:15:15,500
I like you, Bobby.

323
00:15:18,800 --> 00:15:19,367
And...

324
00:15:21,767 --> 00:15:24,433
Right? Let's see.

325
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,167
I want to get to know you,

326
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,100
get to know me too.

327
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:30,067
Who knows,
you might like me too.

328
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,167
If that's okay with you?

329
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:33,833
Waiter!

330
00:15:33,967 --> 00:15:37,233
Can I have a glass of water?
Cold, please.

331
00:15:37,400 --> 00:15:41,133
Oh, but you don't have to
reciprocate it right away.

332
00:15:41,267 --> 00:15:42,133
I'm just wondering,

333
00:15:42,267 --> 00:15:45,600
maybe you'd like
to get to know me more.

334
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:47,533
Let's see where
this will take us.

335
00:15:47,667 --> 00:15:49,100
If that's okay with you.

336
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,400
Hello?

337
00:16:10,533 --> 00:16:13,433
Oh, Grandmother Isang...

338
00:16:13,567 --> 00:16:16,133
This is Tonyo.

339
00:16:16,267 --> 00:16:19,500
Tonyo, who?

340
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,000
Lieutenant Conde,

341
00:16:21,133 --> 00:16:23,733
Bobby's coworker.

342
00:16:23,867 --> 00:16:24,733
Bobby?

343
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:27,133
I don't know Bobby.

344
00:16:27,267 --> 00:16:28,567
Alicia!

345
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:31,333
Alicia!

346
00:16:31,467 --> 00:16:34,200
Oh, Grandmother,
are Mar and Abdul there?

347
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:36,567
Maybe we can talk for a moment.

348
00:16:36,700 --> 00:16:40,200
We're not buying.

349
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:43,533
Grandmother,
we're not selling anything.

350
00:16:43,700 --> 00:16:44,967
So why are you calling?

351
00:16:45,100 --> 00:16:46,267
Oh, it's just an emergency.

352
00:16:46,400 --> 00:16:48,200
Grandmother Isang,
that's my cell phone!

353
00:16:48,333 --> 00:16:50,500
Go ahead and talk to this.
He's hard to talk to.

354
00:16:50,633 --> 00:16:53,600
- Who is this?
- I don't know.

355
00:16:53,733 --> 00:16:55,000
It's Sir Tonyo.

356
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:59,367
Hello, Sir Tonyo?

357
00:16:59,500 --> 00:17:00,533
Hello, hello, Abdul?

358
00:17:00,667 --> 00:17:03,200
Do you know where Jared and
Bobby went on a date?

359
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,533
Oh, I'm sorry.

360
00:17:05,667 --> 00:17:07,800
We're Team Tonyo,
but if you plan on messing up

361
00:17:07,933 --> 00:17:09,500
her and Jared's date,

362
00:17:09,633 --> 00:17:11,767
Oh, it's a no-no for us.

363
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,000
I don't mean to cause trouble.

364
00:17:14,133 --> 00:17:16,767
Bobby, she might be in danger
with Jared

365
00:17:16,933 --> 00:17:18,200
because he's the one
who could have killed

366
00:17:18,333 --> 00:17:20,000
Donabel Custodio.

367
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:22,233
So if you know where they went
on a date,

368
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:23,533
tell me.

369
00:17:23,667 --> 00:17:26,767
- At Cafe Calabari!
- At Cafe Calabari!

370
00:17:26,900 --> 00:17:28,667
Let's go.

371
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:38,067
Jared, sorry, okay.

372
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:40,533
I'll get straight to you.

373
00:17:42,233 --> 00:17:44,933
There's a lot going on
in my life right now.

374
00:17:45,067 --> 00:17:47,467
It's a bit chaotic, and...

375
00:17:48,833 --> 00:17:50,867
you still don't know me
that well.

376
00:17:51,967 --> 00:17:53,633
That's okay, I get it.

377
00:17:54,767 --> 00:17:55,933
You still like Tonyo.

378
00:17:56,067 --> 00:17:57,700
Hey, no!

379
00:17:57,833 --> 00:17:59,433
No, Sir. No, no, no.

380
00:17:59,567 --> 00:18:01,600
So you don't like Tonyo?

381
00:18:01,733 --> 00:18:03,433
Not in that way.

382
00:18:04,367 --> 00:18:06,367
What?

383
00:18:08,400 --> 00:18:09,600
Okay, okay.

384
00:18:11,733 --> 00:18:13,500
Sir, I'll admit
something to you.

385
00:18:17,533 --> 00:18:19,000
Let's be careful, Bro, okay.

386
00:18:19,133 --> 00:18:21,500
This is not our territory.

387
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:26,367
Wait, Bro.

388
00:18:31,233 --> 00:18:33,167
I think I recognize one of them.

389
00:18:34,433 --> 00:18:35,333
Who among them?

390
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:36,967
There...

391
00:18:37,600 --> 00:18:39,067
the one playing checkers.

392
00:18:42,367 --> 00:18:43,867
<i> What have I done to you?</i>

393
00:18:45,667 --> 00:18:47,900
<i> Stay away from Faye Guerrero!</i>

394
00:18:48,033 --> 00:18:49,467
So what are we going to do now?

395
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:54,000
It looks like you need
to exercise.

396
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:55,467
What?

397
00:18:55,633 --> 00:18:55,800
What?

398
00:18:59,533 --> 00:19:01,200
Sir,

399
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:02,867
I'm a cop.

400
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:05,733
and I didn't join
the pageant to win.

401
00:19:07,200 --> 00:19:08,500
We're investigating a case

402
00:19:08,633 --> 00:19:11,100
about the deceased contestant,

403
00:19:11,233 --> 00:19:13,600
It's Donabel Custodio.

404
00:19:13,733 --> 00:19:16,100
Sir, maybe you can help me.

405
00:19:16,233 --> 00:19:17,933
Based on our lead,

406
00:19:18,067 --> 00:19:19,633
there's a good chance that
the person who killed the victim

407
00:19:19,767 --> 00:19:21,567
was a member of the pageant.

408
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:27,133
Bobby...

409
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:30,167
do you really trust me?

410
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:32,800
I wouldn't tell you that, Sir,

411
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:34,500
if I didn't.

412
00:19:38,033 --> 00:19:40,167
Because I also want
to tell you something...

413
00:19:41,300 --> 00:19:42,567
But...

414
00:19:42,700 --> 00:19:43,333
if it's okay,

415
00:19:43,467 --> 00:19:44,667
come with me to my condo first.

416
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:45,833
I'll show you something.

417
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,267
Sir, to your condo?

418
00:19:50,300 --> 00:19:53,400
Yes, but let's eat this first.

419
00:19:53,533 --> 00:19:54,333
This is 3,000 pesos,

420
00:19:54,467 --> 00:19:55,467
it'll be a waste
if we don't finish this.

421
00:19:58,467 --> 00:19:59,400
Roman,

422
00:19:59,533 --> 00:20:00,700
have you spoken
to Okoy yet?

423
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,667
He's not answering, Mayor.

424
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:06,900
Oh, okay, just let me know.

425
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,567
Faye...

426
00:20:14,500 --> 00:20:16,033
Have you been there long?

427
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:18,267
Ah, not really, Glen.

428
00:20:21,167 --> 00:20:22,400
Glen...

429
00:20:24,467 --> 00:20:26,167
just tell me straight.

430
00:20:26,867 --> 00:20:28,600
Don't you like Vince?

431
00:20:29,633 --> 00:20:31,033
Faye.

432
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:33,433
at first,
you were accusing Mommy.

433
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:34,700
Now, it's me.

434
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,767
Glen, it's not like that.

435
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:38,400
I just want to know
what your stand

436
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:40,933
on what's happening to me now.

437
00:20:41,067 --> 00:20:42,433
All you need to know

438
00:20:42,567 --> 00:20:44,867
is that I want
what's best for you.

439
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:46,433
As for Vince,

440
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:49,567
Faye, the world he's living
in is really difficult.

441
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:50,633
If I'm not mistaken,

442
00:20:50,767 --> 00:20:54,033
he used to be
informant and became undercover.

443
00:20:54,167 --> 00:20:56,900
You'll make a lot of enemies
in that job.

444
00:20:57,033 --> 00:21:00,367
It's dangerous, and I don't want
to get you hurt.

445
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:03,100
Okay.

446
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,800
You know, I can send people
to look into it.

447
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,267
Let's do that.

448
00:21:10,733 --> 00:21:12,767
No, brother, It's fine.

449
00:21:14,233 --> 00:21:17,533
I just want to hear
your thoughts.

450
00:21:18,800 --> 00:21:20,267
Come here.

451
00:21:30,167 --> 00:21:31,233
Thank you.

452
00:21:31,933 --> 00:21:33,633
Raise your hands!

453
00:21:33,767 --> 00:21:34,867
- Sir!
- Raise your hands.

454
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:36,033
What's going on?

455
00:21:36,167 --> 00:21:37,100
What's going on here?

456
00:21:37,233 --> 00:21:38,567
I knew it,

457
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:41,200
my suspicions about this jerk
are correct.

458
00:21:41,333 --> 00:21:42,433
What you're doing
is wrong, Tonyo.

459
00:21:42,600 --> 00:21:44,133
Stop it.

460
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:48,067
I'm telling the truth.

461
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:49,867
We're just the same.

462
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,567
I'm also investigating
a murder case here.

463
00:21:58,933 --> 00:22:00,133
Do you think we'll believe you?

464
00:22:00,267 --> 00:22:01,933
I'm telling the truth.

465
00:22:02,067 --> 00:22:04,067
This is what I wanted
to tell you, Bobby, earlier.

466
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:07,200
I'm a private investigator.

467
00:22:07,333 --> 00:22:09,267
Miss Addison
of Add2Cart hired me

468
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,767
to investigate the death
of her daughter.

469
00:22:12,733 --> 00:22:14,900
So why did you invite me
to your condo?

470
00:22:15,067 --> 00:22:15,800
What?

471
00:22:15,933 --> 00:22:17,433
Did you hear that, Tonyo?

472
00:22:17,567 --> 00:22:19,067
Do you find Tonyo
too small?

473
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:20,433
I guess he's belittling you.

474
00:22:20,567 --> 00:22:22,867
Because I want to show
Bobby my work.

475
00:22:23,467 --> 00:22:26,033
After all, we're investigating
the same thing,

476
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:28,000
So maybe we can work
together on this.

477
00:22:29,567 --> 00:22:30,967
Tonyo...

478
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:32,467
Bobby...

479
00:22:32,600 --> 00:22:34,400
Do you believe this?

480
00:22:34,867 --> 00:22:40,000
Do you want to come with me?

481
00:22:45,267 --> 00:22:46,700
Are you sure?

482
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:49,300
This is the one who kill Regan.

483
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:51,433
Yes, Sir, a garbage collector
saw him

484
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:54,067
cutting the CCTV cable.

485
00:22:56,300 --> 00:22:58,667
Everything that's happening
is connected.

486
00:22:58,800 --> 00:22:59,867
Where's Conde?

487
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:01,133
They're not yet here, Sir.

488
00:23:01,267 --> 00:23:04,933
When they arrive, tell them
to report to me immediately.

489
00:23:05,067 --> 00:23:06,900
- Yes, Sir.
- Copy.

490
00:23:07,033 --> 00:23:08,400
Bautista...

491
00:23:09,400 --> 00:23:10,867
Solid police work.

492
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:12,833
- Good job.
- Thank you, Sir.

493
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:15,700
You too, Torres,
De Jesus, good job.

494
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:17,167
- Thank you, Sir.
- Thank you, Sir.

495
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:18,300
Go ahead, dismissed.

496
00:23:28,533 --> 00:23:29,833
Come in.

497
00:23:36,567 --> 00:23:37,833
There.

498
00:23:37,967 --> 00:23:40,033
That's the case
of Sasha Cartega.

499
00:23:41,100 --> 00:23:41,967
After she won

500
00:23:42,100 --> 00:23:44,433
Binibining Calabari
two years ago,

501
00:23:44,933 --> 00:23:46,400
she suddenly died.

502
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:48,367
Drug overdose.

503
00:23:49,167 --> 00:23:50,400
But did you know,

504
00:23:51,067 --> 00:23:52,800
she was never a user.

505
00:23:53,633 --> 00:23:55,467
That's why her mother suspected

506
00:23:55,633 --> 00:23:57,800
that foul play
had really happened.

507
00:23:59,167 --> 00:24:00,733
What do you think, Bok?

508
00:24:01,367 --> 00:24:03,267
Well, if that's her hunch,

509
00:24:03,833 --> 00:24:06,233
why didn't she ask
the police for help,

510
00:24:06,367 --> 00:24:08,733
Instead of going to a private
investigator?

511
00:24:09,933 --> 00:24:11,633
He approached you.

512
00:24:12,167 --> 00:24:14,233
Right at Station 12.

513
00:24:15,233 --> 00:24:16,800
But she feels like

514
00:24:17,467 --> 00:24:18,367
it just trying to cover it up
by the police officer

515
00:24:18,500 --> 00:24:20,833
in charge of the case
so it won't be solved.

516
00:24:21,800 --> 00:24:24,367
So she lost her trust in you.

517
00:24:24,967 --> 00:24:27,433
Do you know who that police
officer is?

518
00:24:37,167 --> 00:24:40,033
Lieutenant Regan Robles.

519
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,533
We didn't come here
to cause trouble.

520
00:25:02,700 --> 00:25:03,600
We just want to know

521
00:25:03,733 --> 00:25:05,033
who ordered you to beat me up.

522
00:25:05,167 --> 00:25:06,300
Is that all you need from me?

523
00:25:06,433 --> 00:25:08,233
They already know
we're investigating this.

524
00:25:08,367 --> 00:25:10,133
That means they're watching us.

525
00:25:10,267 --> 00:25:11,233
What are you planning, Sir?

526
00:25:11,367 --> 00:25:14,533
The question is, Jared,
are you good at acting?

527
00:25:14,667 --> 00:25:16,100
I'm innocent!

528
00:25:16,233 --> 00:25:17,133
Let me go!

529
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:19,400
Mayor, we can move freely now.

530
00:25:19,533 --> 00:25:21,867
No one will make a decision
without my go signal.

531
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:23,733
There are big investors
coming in.

532
00:25:23,867 --> 00:25:26,067
I want things to run
as smooth as possible.

533
00:25:26,200 --> 00:25:27,467
So, girls, are you ready?

534
00:25:27,600 --> 00:25:29,667
Because we are about to start
